Below is an instruction that describes a task. Write a response that appropriately completes the request.

### Instruction:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Response:

This command sets up a secure shell (SSH) connection to an Amazon EC2 instance using the specified key file and creates a local forwarding tunnel from port 25900 on your local machine to port 5900 on the remote server. The user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com is the hostname of the EC2 instance you want to connect to, and "~/.UserKey.pem" specifies the path to your private key file that will be used for authentication. The "-C" option enables compression on the forwarding tunnel, while the "-L" option creates a local port forwarding rule.
